name: Honesty
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
She said, "Baby, I'm afraid to fall in love
Cause what if it's not reciprocated?"
I told her, "Don't rush girl, dont you rush
Guess it's all a game of patience."

[Pre-Chorus]
She said, "What if I dive deep?
Will you come in after me?
Would you share your flaws with me? Let me know."
I told her, "Thinking is all wrong
Love will happen when it wants
I know it hurts sometimes, but don't let it go."

[Chorus]
'Cause I want you, I want you, I want- I want you
'Cause I want you, I want you, I want- I want you

[Verse 2]
She said, "What if I tell you all the things I've done?
Would you run away from me?"
I told her, "Baby, we all got bags full of shit that we don't want
But I can't unpack it for you, baby."

[Pre-Chorus]
She said, "What if I dive deep?
Will you come in after me?
Would you share your flaws with me? Let me know."
I told her, "Thinking is all wrong
Love will happen when it wants
I know it hurts sometimes, but don't let it go."
[Chorus]
'Cause I want you, I want you, I want- I want you
'Cause I want you, I want you, I want- I want you, yeah
I want you, I want you, I want you, yeah
annotations:
[('But I can’t unpack it for you, baby.”', [['“Honesty” decodes the feelings between two individuals who are interested in each other. The girl has been hurt before and is reluctant to give love another try.
Pink Sweat$ touches on an important subject regarding on when someone is starting a new relationship in this line
“ We all got bags full of shit we don’t want
But I can’t unpack it for you baby.”
Everyone has baggage and subconscious fears that wear us down. However, we as individuals cannot rely on our significant other to lift the weight of that baggage.
Pink Sweat$, a person of growth and wisdom, is teaching his new love interest this important concept as she moves forward and learns to trust again.']]), ('She said, ”What if I dive deep?
 Will you come in after me?
 Would you share your flaws with me? Let me know.”
 I told her, ”Thinking is all wrong
 Love will happen when it wants
 I know it hurts sometimes, but don’t let it go.”', [['If I do everything you ask of me, will the feelings be mutual? Commitment is a two way street.']]), ('She said, ”Baby, I’m afraid to fall in love
 Cause what if it’s not reciprocated?”
 I told her, ”Don’t rush girl, dont you rush
 Guess it’s all a game of patience.”', [['This verse is based on a girl I know. She was always so afraid to love, and I wanted her to know there’s nothing to be scared of. You cant force it… it just happens.']]), ('I told her, ”Baby, we all got bags full of shit that we don’t want', [['We all have some hidden secrets, some regrets that we don’t want in our life but sometimes sharing them seems the end of them.']])]

annotations:
[('TBD', [['Trouble’s Edgewood is underrated']]), ('TBD', [['“Romance” by Ex:Re



Ex:Re is the name Elena Tonra from Daughter used to post her album with the same title, it means ‘regarding ex’, and also ‘X-Ray’, as a way to look inside. She described the song as the details of a night where intimacy felt kind of cold, where she was trying to find something in someone that wasn’t there.

I thought of another the whole time
Who would have never stared me like that
See, he saw me as a human
This one thinks I’m a slaughterhouse

The track itself is alternative/experimental pop and it’s really an experience, like the whole album. There’s so much too process and to take in, it all comes crashing down as you hear her story. The way this song makes you feel, it’s another level.

Romance is dead and done
And it hits between the eyes on this side
The grass is dead and barren
And it hurts between my thighs on this side']]), ('TBD', [['XXXTENTACION Skins']]), ('6 Dogs, “Buttcheeks”', [['I feel like this should be at least on the lower end of the top 65 list. It is a nice breath of fresh air from all the formulaic pop-rap songs and the same mainstream rappers that are featured everywhere else throughout albums and tracks.']]), ('TBD', [['wish there was room for one of the cuts off of Bianca’s Can’t Wait EP, like the one that is making traction “Ringtone”']]), ('TBD', [['LIFE’S A TRIP by Trippie Redd anyone?']]), ('TBD', [['Charlie Heat – “Celebrate Life” ft. DRAM & Ant Beale']]), ('Migos, “Stir Fry”', [['why aren’t we talking about this song? came out 12/20/2017 so too late for last list and didn’t really blow up until 2018. could easily switch with a song on the existing list (“mo bamba”, “psycho”) but should be top 30']]), ('Trippie Redd, A Love Letter To You 3', [['ALLTY 3 rapped up the trilogy as it should have. From the beautiful production on Topanga to the intimate singing on Camp Fire Tale, this album keeps that energy throughout the album. I don’t see anything topping his debut, but this album is a really strong effort that continues to make Trippie a driving a force. Pretty good at this spot as is']]), ('TBD', [['Vacation in Hell by Flatbush Zombies?']])]

annotations:
[('[Produced by Ludwig Göransson]', [['Sonically, this song is very similar to 80s Synthpop/R&B. Very similar to Michael Jackson in particular.



“It’s Michael Jackson-esque,” Gambino said about “Sober” in Sept. 2014.']]), ('’Cause I know', [['This line is referring to the fact that Glover now knows that he will never be “sober” because he knows he is drunk in love with this girl and believes he will stay drunk in love with her for the rest of his life – even after their possible break up.']]), ('Girl, if it’s done right
 Well you know it’s got to be, something wonderful to me', [['If a new relationship is done right, it will mean and will be something wonderful to Childish Gambino.

Gambino has had a history of bad relationships, which one almost lead to his death after a bad breakup. So this may also mean, he’s done settling in relationships which is why it has to be wonderful for him.']]), ('Oh honey now girl, give it one night
 If you just give it a chance, loving you is not my plan', [['Gambino has some unsaid plans that do not include having sex; instead, he wants to show this girl their true potential, one that cannot be defined by a mere one-night stand. If this girl gives what they have going on a chance for a night.']]), ('If you let it shine, you can free your mind', [['If the girl lets go of all her worries that they might not work out or of her past thoughts of Donald, maybe their relationship could be something like this']]), ('And now that it’s over, I’ll never be sober
 I couldn’t believe, but now I’m so high
 But now I’m so high
 But now I’m so high
 But now I’m so high', [['While Gambino has been one to let his feelings out, on this occasion he hates being sober, (even though he’s cooled down on the bottle), and would rather use the world’s vices to get him out of the dumps.

He’s always had fears about his girl leaving him. This could have been made around the time the girl Donald wanted to marry broke up with him:

We went to Australia and I was just super depressed. I mean, I tried to kill myself. I was really fucked up after that, because I had this girl that I thought I was going to marry and we broke up. I didn’t feel like I knew what I was doing.

http://youtu.be/gnwuYYJ9_SU?t=30s']]), ('And now that it’s over, I’ll never be sober', [['After a possible breakup with a girl, Donald is going to get over his emotions by indulging in alcohol and getting drunk, which takes him to a different reality. However, he believes he’ll never get over her so he’s going to never stop drinking.

Also, the girl’s love is his drug. Now that it’s “over”, he acknowledges how he’ll always keep coming back for more. Furthermore, he’s foreshadowing a relapse into her addicting love.

This could also be referring to him being constantly high and never coming down from that high (and being sober). That could be a more likely idea because as Glover has said himself, he’s stopped drinking for the most part.

It’s possible that the beginning line of “And now that it’s over” is referring to him waking up at the end of the STN MTN mixtape, and is continuing on from that onto the Kauai EP.']]), ('If you just give me some time I can open up your mind', [['Gambino is asking this girl for the most precious thing we have as humans: time. Spending some time with Gambino however could allow any girl to become just a bit wiser.

This could also play into the bigger idea of getting high. Seeing as how high Gambino is from the hook, he could also open up this girl’s mind by getting her high.']]), ('(I want to be the only one)', [['Gambino is saying he wants to be the only one that girl is interested in.



This is directly relating to the fact in the song “Melrose” he says that “Someone gave you all my love”, he wants to be the only on giving that love to her.']]), ('Cause I know one day you’ll see
 All the things that we can be', [['If his girl actually took time to think about what things would be like in the future, she would know the endless possibilities of their relationship. Donald knows one day she’ll realize what she’s missing out on.']])]

[('You’re to blame for what we could have been

 I’m not scared of it, she ain’t either
 Why second guess? I should have stayed
 ’Cause you know what’s on my mind so', [['A common symptom of “teenage fever” is simply indecisiveness, which leads to hesitation as a person is unsure whether romantic feelings are mutual, due to a lack of experience in the dating game.

Even though Drake has an incredible amount of experience with romance; from dating pop star Rihanna to world tennis champion Serena Williams, and most recently Jennifer Lopez, and the fact he’s a worldwide superstar, the girl he’s just met is forcing him back into the position of the common teenager, suffering from the infamous “teenage fever.”']]), ('I met someone new last night and we kicked it
 And I’m going back there tonight
 And you know what’s on my mind, this time
 Going back there tonight
 And you know what’s on my mind so', [['Since Drake’s love interest is unresponsive to his emotional signals, he’s spending time with another woman, likely to take his mind off of the troubles of unfulfilled romance.

 But girl, we both thought it
 Why second guess? I should have stayed
 You say the word, I’m on the way', [['They didn’t say they wanted to have sex with each other, but the look in their eyes was enough that they both knew.

Unfortunately for Drake, he hesitated and did not take that chance to make a move on her, so the night ended with him leaving. Anyone who’s had feelings for someone can relate to this, especially when it’s uncertain if the other person shares the same feelings as Drake probably thought.

Looking back at that moment, he regrets second-guessing the situation. He tries to relieve his inner turmoil by telling her that, if she gives him that vibe again, he will be ready for that opportunity again.']]), ('Your heart is hard to carry after dark', [["The expression, ‘carry your heart,’ was popularized by e. e. cummings' poem, “I carry your heart with me(i carry it in my heart)”. It refers to the kind of deep and profound love.

Drake has trouble maintaining the integrity of this sensual love late at night when there is ample temptation, and before the end of the verse, he finds another love interest.

He’s likely having trouble with love because of the relationship problems he describes in the first verse; arguing, cheating, and selfishness."]]), ('[Chorus: Jennifer Lopez]

 That your love would be untrue
 Would you lie to me?', [['This chorus was sampled from American singer Jennifer Lopez’s 1999 hit “If You Had My Love.” from her album On The 6.

Drake and Lopez were rumored to be dating after posting photos and videos together on their social media accounts a few months before the release of More Life. In an appearance on The Ellen Show, Lopez confirmed that the duo had collaborated, but she was unsure of where the track would end up.

https://youtu.be/op_BiLgnAwY?t=4m10s

Since this chorus is sampled, it’s likely that this isn’t the song Lopez referred to, and their impending collaboration is still yet to come.']]), ('Your friends are scared to tell you, you went too far
 Funny that it’s always been all about you from the start', [['Drake and his love interest are at a breaking point in their relationship. In the previous line he blames her for their current status, suggesting her behavior has created mistrust and hostility.

When people argue they often do or say things to hurt one another, and “taking it too far” means the girl has gone beyond the bounds of arguing, causing irreparable damage to the relationship. Her friends are hesitant to tell her the truth about her actions, likely because they want to remain supportive.

Drake recalls that since the start of the relationship she has been very self-centered, instead of reciprocating his love. This is likely why he seeks new companionship in the next line.']]), ('Out of body
 That’s just how I feel when I’m around you, shawty', [['An out-of-body experience is an experience that typically involves a feeling of floating outside one’s body and, in some cases, the feeling of perceiving one’s physical body as if from a place outside one’s body.

Drake is saying that when he is around this girl, it feels like his soul leaves his body as if he’s divine. This sounds like an extreme case of the butterflies.

Surprisingly, this sounds similar to the feeling Drake described in 2010 when talking about Rihanna.']]), ('[Outro: Dave]
 Yeah, slightly took a left turn there

 More ideas and stuff comin’
 Yeah, yeah, fam
 I’m wafflin’, but man is tired, fam, Jesus Christ', [['Santan Dave, also known simply as Dave, is a British rapper hailing from South London. His lyrics touch upon conscious topics such as decision-making and inspiring fellow young people to become who they want to be.

Already an established artist in the UK by the time of the release of More Life, he gained attention overseas when Drake remixed his song “Wanna Know” and premiered it on OVO Sound Radio.

Dave explained to Ebro that he was unaware that the voice note would appear on the album, and it was a genuine conversation he’d been having:

https://youtu.be/yEH6IU7pDOg?t=1778']])]

annotations:
[('The kind I lose it all for', [['What does it mean to lose it all for?']]), ('Good gir', [['What is a Good Girl? When Karlie Kloss debuted for the Good Girl Perfume Commercial Campaign in 2017, she contributed to a new image of the Good Girl; A Hard-Working Feminine Woman Chasing Her Dreams with a mystery that is as unique as the tones of the Perfume. Our perception of the Good Girl is challenged by this singers persistent focus of attention on the inner qualities of this girl; She has inherent inner qualities that make her appealing to the singer. There is no mention of her sexuality or promiscuity. Nothing to do with how she presents herself. Instead, the soulful song has an emphasis on what a Good Girl she is and how that makes the singer feel about her; he falls deeply and passionately for her even though he is not with her.']]), ('In another time, in another place
 You would be mine', [['We believe that being in the same Time and Space Continuum is enough to forge a connection between two human beings. The starting verse of this song leads us to believe that this is perhaps the only thing keeping the singer away from his love interest. The Melancholic tone of his voice gives away his sadness. He might not believe this about himself. When we think of being with someone, we think of physical presence, we think of time and place. The singer has led us to believe he has neither of these, yet hopes, albeit unconvincingly that his lover could meet him differently if he had Time and Space.']]), ('On a brighter day, under a different sky
 Maybe we’d fly', [['On “You Can’t Save Me”, SiR sings about about meeting the perfect person at the wrong time. In this line, he says “on a brighter day, under a different sky, maybe we’d fly”, which describes the feeling that if the circumstances were different, and SiR was in a better place to accept the love, maybe they’d be a successful match.

If you pay close attention, you’ll notice that only a few tracks later is a song titled “New Sky”, which is about meeting a girl that he feels like he’s met before and has a connection with already. Possibly the same girl from this track.']]), ('Yes, I was in the wrong place at the wrong time with the right one', [['A major recurrent theme throughout the album includes SiR noting how he finds himself caught in the wrong time for certain situations and relationships.

In an interview with DJBooth, SiR explains"

…I think we have less control over destiny than we wanna give credit sometimes…Timing is everything, but nothing happens when I want it to. Everything happens in God’s terms.']])]

name: Her
lyrics:
[Chorus]
I got her, in the palm of, my hand
She knows I love her
I got her, thought I lost her, again

[Verse 1]
But life's so quick, sometimes
Just blinking you might miss it when you close, your eyes
It's been, a while, since we kicked it but the answer's on her lips tonight
[Chorus]
I got her, in the palm of, my hand
She knows I love her
I got her, thought I lost her, again

[Verse 2]
I'm on, the way
To finding out exactly how to treat her right
Another day, and I've been waiting
But I've been waiting my whole life, to find
Someone like her
[Chorus]
I got her, in the palm of, my hand
She knows I love her
I got her, thought I lost her, again
[Verse 3]
I'm glad we made it this far
Sometimes you just don't know
So many days spent apart but now
I'm finally yours (so won't you)

[Bridge]
Move my body, do it right
Left, right, side, side
Not about to waste my time, waiting all night
Move my body, do it right
Left, right, side, side
Not about to waste my time, waiting all night
[Chorus]
I got her, in the palm of, my hand
She knows I love her
I got her, thought I lost her, again
[Outro]
She knows I got her
She knows I love her
She knows I got her
She knows I love her
She knows, she does
But it's cool because
It's me she loves
She knows, she does
annotations:

The lyrics and beat give gigantic clues about this mood. Don’t read other lyrics explanations down there, they are all off track!']]), ('Not about to waste my time, waiting all night', [['He’s been waiting all night for this moment and he hopes she doesn’t waste his time.']]), ('Move my body, do it right
 Left, right, side, side', [['He’s talking about them making love with each other']]), ('I’m on, the way
 To finding out exactly how to treat her right', [['From the hook we can tell that he is talking about a girl who he has been with before and maybe had a bad relationship with, but she has given him another chance – “I got her, thought I lost her, again”.
So he is now trying to learn how to treat her better so that he doesn’t lose her again this time.']]), ('(so won’t you)', [['Leads us into the bridge. They’re about to get it in!']]), ('So many days spent apart but now
 I’m finally yours', [['They have spent time apart, but now they are together. He is hers and she can now do whatever she wants with him…']]), ('I’m glad we made it this far
 Sometimes you just don’t know', [['Majid is in love with this girl and he is glad their relationship has come so far, especially because of how futile relationships can be.

In the next line we see that they have spent some time apart, which makes this feat of staying together even more profound.']]), ('[Outro]
 She knows I got her
 She knows I love her
 She knows I got her
 She knows I love her
 She knows, she does
 But it’s cool because
 It’s me she loves
 She knows, she does', [['As much as she denies it to her friends and him, he is the one she will always love. She knows it.']]), ('Another day, and I’ve been waiting
 But I’ve been waiting my whole life, to find
 Someone like her', [['This girl who left him has a grip on his heart. He has been waiting for someone like her to come into his life, someone who was as great as she was.']]), ('It’s been, a while, since we kicked it but the answer’s on her lips tonight', [['It’s been awhile since they have hung out and connected, but the way they kiss is just the same. They can still feel the same way regardless of the distance they have experienced.']])]

In the film, Detective Shame (Wayans) develops feelings for a much younger Peaches (Pinkett Smith), who was 16 when they first met. When Peaches is 22, going on 23, Shame decides to work with her and the two become romantically involved.']]), ('Dragged me like two hours to your family’s house, for what?', [['Drake booked multiple shows in London at 02 Arena in 2017, and Jorja Smith lives in London. London to Walsall is about a two hour drive.']]), ('Already got what you needed, I guess', [['Drake collaborated with Jorja Smith on two tracks—“Jorja Interlude” and “Get It Together,” from his 2017 playlist, More Life.  I do for a living but is way less wavy', [['In a 2018 Billboard interview, Jorja revealed that she was dating Joel Compass, a singer from London:

[('Told me, “Get well,” did you mean that? ’Cause I can’t tell
 I ain’t feelin’ well, kept it in, then my tears fell', [['After Tiller reaches out to his ex, she responds with a “get well”, indicating she is aware Tiller hasn’t been feeling his best. Tiller is questioning that she really cares about his well-being or that she is being genuine. This is likely due to it being a one sided breakup to where Tiller is left feeling like he doesn’t really know this person anymore and doubting that she truly cares for him.']]), ('Inhale, exhale, yeah
 I might take another hit before I set sail', [["In his opening lines, Tiller seems to be preparing for a potentially stressful situation. He start’s by saying “inhale, exhale”, which is a practice often used in meditation. This breathing technique can help alleviate anxiety, tension, and stress.

The song also samples Mary J. Blige’s “Not Gon' Cry” and SWV’s “All Night Long” from 1995’s Waiting to Exhale soundtrack. Inhale, Exhale is also a play on words and a nod to the greats used in the making of the song.

In the second verse, Tiller refers to taking a “hit” before he “set’s sail”. Taking a hit is often in reference to a joint of marijuana – something also commonly used to alleviate stress – while setting sail is used to represent the act of leaving for somewhere.

The tornado is one of two references to the classic novel/movie “The Wizard of Oz” in this song, in which the main character Dorothy is swept away into the Land of Oz by a tornado.

Once you put those two references together, and mix water with a tornado, you get a highly influential event that happened to Ocean. After hurricane Katrina hit his hometown of New Orleans, Frank moved to Los Angeles to chase his dream of being a musician.

Over my family I put you first
Writing out my feelings is the only thing that work
I don't hear from the friends I thought were mine too
But I hold on to the poems I would write you
Happy seventeen, I saw us two and you saw three
I guess our lines are structured like a haiku
[Chorus 2
You got me shot down by love
And you got my heart now
Why won't you stop now?
Oh I've been knocked down by you
And you got my heart now
Why won't you stop now?

[Bridge]
Knocked down, knocked down
Knocked down, knocked down
Knocked down
Knocked down

[Chorus]
I've been shot down by love
You got my heart now
Why won't you stop now?
I've been knocked down by you
And you got my heart now
Why won't you stop now?
annotations:
[('Writing out my feelings is the only thing that work', [['Writing is a very common mechanism for coping with emotions. As is said in Another Sad Love Song, Khalid puts his feelings into his music in order to deal with them.

I’m not the best at showing my emotions…
I guess this sounds like another sad love song
I can’t get over how it all went wrong
But, I let the words come together
Then, maybe I’ll feel better.']]), ('You got my heart now
 Why won’t you stop now?
 Oh I’ve been knocked down by you
 You got my heart now
 Why won’t you stop now?', [['He is continuously falling in love and finds something new to love in his lover all the time. He can not comprehend why his love for this person keeps on growing. “Knocked down” implies that he has fallen hard or that this love that he has for this person has hit him hard (it is strong and was unexpected).

Because the love he has for her is so real, her decision to leave has knocked him down and he is at an all time low.']]), ('I would die for you', [['You put all of yourself into someone. “I’m giving you all of me. I’m giving you all this dedication. I would die for you. But am I all that you need? ’Cause you’re all that I need.”']]), ('We’ve been here before, surrounded in the cold', [['It’s like, “I’ve been there before. We’ve been there before. We’ve both been through this situation.” “We’ve both been through the heartbreak and pain. But somehow, you were the one who made me open up.” “You were the one who made me get over everything. You were the one who made me feel happy. And now you want to leave?” That hurts.”']]), ('Happy seventeen, I saw us two and you saw three
 I guess our lines are structured like a haiku', [['We’re teenagers. You saw me. You saw somebody else. It’s triangular. I thought that was very clever. I felt like a rapper.']]), ('Happy seventeen, I saw us two and you saw three
 I guess our lines are structured like a haiku', [['We’re teenagers. You saw me. You saw somebody else. It’s triangular. I thought that was very clever. I felt like a rapper.'], ['A haiku is a form of poetry with a specific structure. It can only have three lines with a total of 17 syllables: five in the first, seven in the second and five in the last one.

A cool thing to note is that the haiku pattern can (almost) be seen at the beginning of the chorus:

5- “You got me shot down
7- By love, (and) you got my heart now,
5- Why won’t you stop now”']])]

annotations:
[('Green Day - “Still Breathing”', [['The third single and seventh track from Green Day’s twelfth studio album Revolution Radio.

Since it was coincidentally released on the fourth year anniversary of the so-called “iHeart Radio Incident,” which resulted in lead singer/guitarist/songwriter Billie Joe Armstrong being sent to rehab, Armstrong was asked in a Rolling Stones interview if his personal life contributed to the writing of “Still Breathing,” to which he responded:

I don’t wanna be selfish. [Laughs] I’d rather write something where my eyes are forward, not so much internal. I hope it makes people happy and creates a difference in some way, just by people recognizing themselves in the song.

The song has also been questioned to be about Armstrong’s battle with drug addiction, which is true but also not. Armstrong spoke about this idea in a radio interview:

It’s about losing something…where the chaos of life makes sense. Life isn’t perfect, it’s better than that. I you can survive through some of this stuff, you find out who you really are, whether its drug addiction, losing a family member or dealing with somebody who has some serious personality issues. It goes from the life of a junkie and a gambler to the life of a single mother to the life of a soldier…[it’s about] how we’re all intertwined with that…its universal.

Which leads me to discuss how this song deserves a spot here. This song not only relates to me but many of Green Day’s fans, whether they’re recovering from an addiction or depression. This song can give them hope for a brighter tomorrow or give them inspiration to be able to say, “I’m still breathing on my own.”']]), ('Green Day - “Bang Bang”', [['The second track and first single released from Green Day’s twelfth studio album Revolution Radio.

Though not an extremely extremely political jam compared to their rock opera American Idiot back in 2004, the song does discuss many details of mass shootings in the US and around the world.

When asked about “Bang Bang” in a Rolling Stone interview, vocalist/guitarist Billie Joe Armstrong responded:

It’s about the culture of mass shooting that happens in America mixed with narcissistic social media. There’s this sort of rage happening, but it’s also now being filmed and we all have ourselves under surveillance. To me, that is so twisted. To get into the brain of someone like that was freaky. It freaked me out. After I wrote it, all I wanted to do was get that out of my brain because it just freaked me out.']]), ('YEAHTIM - “No More Staffin’ On RG”', [['Is it too late to put this number one?']]), ('Rich Chigga - Who That Be', [['Name a more iconic song that came out this year. Don’t worry, I’ll wait.']]), ('Aesop Rock - “Kirby”', [["Okay so I know that there’s next to no chance that this track is going to make it to the top 50 whatsoever, but I want to nominate it anyway. #ForTheWeirdos

This song is so cool: how many people rap about cats? Aes' lyrics are really well thought out for such a nerdy yet endearing concept, and his idiosyncratic verbosity (yes that’s an ironic statement) doesn’t interfere with the subject matter to a point where you need to be a total genius putting a lot of effort in just to understand it.

The beat has really nice drippy vibe to it and isn’t too dusty for just a casual listen. “Kirby” is a really well balanced song, quirky and eye-catching, and to me well deserving of a top 50 spot."]]), ('PIKOTARO - “Pen Pineapple Apple Pen”', [['Pen Pineapple Apple Pen was released in 2016 and became a meme somehow, even charting on Billboard.']]), ('Gnash - “​i​ hate u, i love u”', [['I LOVE this song. great lyrics, great production, great vocals all around. compared to the competition it probably won’t get too high on the list if it makes it, but i’d love to have a top 70.']]), ('Bloc Party - “Different Drugs”', [['this song sounds like it could be a collab with the xx. luscious, spaced out guitars and vocal delivery in short bursts. in fact, it strongly resembles the xx song “chained.”

this is without a doubt the biggest triumph on HYMNS, with Kele claiming he wants to revive a relationship but recognising that there’s no way it can be rekindled without some kind of artificial enhancement. sad.']]), ('Alicia Keys - Pawn It All', [['my personal favorite on HERE. very catchy, very soulful. gospel meets hip-hop. neo-soul at its best. the only reason why i would see this making our list is that it’s an excellent representative of this modern gospel sort of genre. the melody recalls some old spirituals.']]), ('Alicia Keys - Holy War', [['deeply moving track on HERE; it’s pretty affecting and she gets really real and vulnerable on it. it’s a standout, for sure; her vocals soar, imperfect to the point of perfection. such a beautiful, beautiful song. 60s, if anything.']])]

name: I Fall Apart
lyrics:
[Intro]
Ooh, I fall apart
Ooh, yeah, mmm, yeah

[Verse 1]
She told me that I'm not enough (Yeah)
And she left me with a broken heart (Yeah)
She fooled me twice and it's all my fault (Yeah)
She cut too deep, now she left me scarred (Yeah)
Now there's so many thoughts goin' through my brain (Yeah)
And now I'm takin' these shots like it's Novocaine, yeah

[Chorus]
Ooh, I fall apart
Down to my core
Ooh, I fall apart
Down to my core
Ooh, didn't know it before
Surprised when you caught me off guard
All this damn jewelry I bought
You was my shorty, I thought

[Verse 2]
Never caught a feelin' this hard
Harder than the liquor I pour
Tell me you don't want me no more
But I can't let go, everybody told me so
Feelin' like I sold my soul
Devil in the form of a whore
Devil in the form of a whore
You said it, no, you said it
No, you said that shit, we'd be together, oh
[Chorus]
Ooh, I fall apart
Down to my core
Ooh, I fall apart
Down to my core
Ooh, didn't know it before
Surprised when you caught me off guard
All this damn jewelry I bought
You was my shorty, I thought

[Bridge]
Ice keep pourin' and the drink keep flowin'
Try to brush it off, but it keep on goin'
Covered in scars and I can't help showin'
Whippin' in the foreign and the tears keep rollin'
Ice keep droppin' and the drink keep flowin'
Try to brush it off, but it keep on goin'
All these scars, can't help from showin'
Whippin' in the foreign and the tears keep blowin', yeah

[Chorus]
Ooh, I fall apart
Down to my core
Ooh, I fall apart
Down to my core
Ooh, didn't know it before
Surprised when you caught me off guard
All this damn jewelry I bought
You was my shorty, I thought
annotations:
[('All this damn jewelry I bought', [['Post Malone is no stranger when it comes to buying expensive and extravagant materialistic items to show off. In his April 2016 song, “Go Flex,” he dedicates the whole track on his rise to fame and showcases his jewelry:

Man, I just wanna go flex
Gold on my teeth and on my neck

In an interview with HOT 97, Post recognized his fondness of jewelry:

You know ever since I was a little kid, I really – I know I wanted gold teeth. I mean I always loved like shiny stuff, that’s just like – you know what I’m into']]), ('Whippin’ in the foreign and the tears keep rollin’', [['Not even in his expensive foreign car can Post drive away from his problems and sadness.



Malone is known for his penchant for expensive cars. This isn’t the first time that he’s talked about pricey rides; he has also done this in his feature on “Foreign” with Jazz Laser and Mally Mall.

Foreign, foreign, foreign, foreign
You get off early in the morning
I be in valet, I’m cool with the drivers
He see my car and he already know it']]), ('Ice keep pourin’ and the drink keep flowin’', [['Post is shocked at the sudden loss of the woman he loves. Many people turn to drinking when they lose somebody, either through a breakup, death, or other circumstances. This can result from the inability to cope with stress, depression, and life in general.

As with many men before him, this woman leaving his life drives Post to drink away his pain. He tries to get past his feelings, but his willpower is no match for a cold glass of whiskey.']]), ('She fooled me twice and it’s all my fault (Yeah)', [['After he fell in love with her once, he should have learned from the experience of a previous break-up so he accepts responsibility for the pain he’s going through. This is a reference to the old proverb:

Fool me once, shame on you; fool me twice, shame on me.

Which became even more popular after President George W. Bush misquoted it on September 17, 2002 in Nashville, Tennessee.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eKgPY1adc0A']]), ('Never caught a feelin’ this hard
 Harder than the liquor I pour', [['Post Malone uses the specific verb “catch” in the same way he would say he “caught” some ill or disease that caused him harm and injury.

Hard liquor means a higher alcohol content resulting in drunkenness faster. Post relates this to how hard he fell for the girl, as well as touching on his use of alcohol as an escape.

In the end, the feelings he has are “harder” and therefore we can assume that alcohol doesn’t help the situation.']]), ('Feelin’ like I sold my soul
 Devil in the form of a whore
 Devil in the form of a whore', [['Selling your soul means sacrificing good morals for something you desire. Religiously it means making a deal with the devil to burn in hell in return for certain things in life.

Post relates his ex to the devil, explaining how it feels like he sold his soul to her, yet all he was awarded was heartbreak.']]), ('And now I’m takin’ these shots like it’s Novocaine, yeah', [['Novocaine is an anesthetic used quite frequently in medical work and dentistry. When used, it creates a pain-numbing effect, allowing Post to numb the heartbreak he is going through.  As Post takes shots of alcohol, it makes him feel numb like Novocaine when he’s under the influence.

Post is also so used to the belittling, verbal shots and insults taken at him that he’s become numb and can no longer be hurt by them. This relates to the well-known saying: “sticks and stones may break my bones but words will never hurt me”.']])]

name: Doing It Wrong
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
When a good thing goes bad it's not the end of the world
It's just the end of a world that you had with one girl
And she's the reason it happened, but she's overreacting
And it's all because she don't want things to change

[Chorus]
So cry if you need to, but I can't stay to watch you
That's the wrong thing to do
Touch if you need to, but I can't stay to hold you
That's the wrong thing to do
Talk if you need to, but I can't stay to hear you
That's the wrong thing to do
Cause you'll say you love me, and I'll end up lying
And say I love you, too

[Bridge]
But I need someone different
You know it, oh ho, you know it
Oh ho, you know it, we both know it
I need someone different
You know it, oh ho, you know it
Oh ho, you know it, we both know it
Something's been missing
You know it, oh ho, she knows it
Oh ho, I know it, we all know it
I need someone different
(Oh ho, oh ho)
[Verse 2]
We live in a generation of not being in love
And not being together
But we sure make it feel like we're together
Because we're scared to see each other with somebody else

[Chorus]
So cry if you need to, but I can't stay to watch you
That's the wrong thing to do
Touch if you need to, but I can't stay to hold you
That's the wrong thing to do
Talk if you need to, but I can't stay to hear you
That's the wrong thing to do
Cause you'll say you love me, and I'll end up lying
And say I love you, too

[Bridge]
But I need someone different
You know it, oh ho, you know it
Oh ho, you know it, we both know it
I need someone different
You know it, oh ho, you know it
Oh ho, you know it, we both know it
Something's been missing
You know it, oh ho, she knows it
Oh ho, I know it, we all know it
I need someone different
(Oh ho, oh ho)
[Outro: Stevie Wonder on Harmonica]
annotations:
[('Cause you’ll say you love me, and I’ll end up lying
 And say I love you, too', [['Drake cares about this girl so deeply that he holds himself back in order to prevent leading the girl on, and hurting her even more.

Cause you’ll say you love me…

By doing the things Drake states he can’t do in the previous lines, the girl may be lead on.

…and I’ll end up lying

However, Drake doesn’t feel the same way for some reason and will tell a lie which, in his opinion, is the lesser of two evils.

And say I love you, too

Drake knows that if it comes to this situation, he won’t be able to break her heart and tell her that he doesn’t feel the same way, ultimately hurting her even more in the long run.']]), ('And she’s the reason it happened, but she’s overreacting
 And it’s all because she don’t want things to change', [['A breakup situation depends on the couple. Drake is blaming his girl for the problems they had and it made their relationship sour.']]), ('But I need someone different
 You know it, oh ho, you know it
 Oh ho, you know it, we both know it
 I need someone different
 You know it, oh ho, you know it
 Oh ho, you know it, we both know it', [['The girl is indeed someone he cares for, but his assertion that he needs someone different is less about “variety” and more about being with the right person. This is further evidenced with the “something’s been missing” line.

He repeatedly expresses remorse over the breakup…but acknowledges that it was necessary for both parties.']]), ('I need someone different', [['Drake has moved on. He knows this isn’t the girl for him. He may think he should try and make it work with this girl, but he is aware of the fact that in the long run this isn’t the girl for him. He repeats this throughout the song, like he is convincing himself instead of convincing the girl.

Your friendly neighborhood editor, iceberg, is an expert on this feeling. He gets over girls while they still love him more than ever for no reason other than his money, rapping skills, sweaters and disarming good looks.']]), ('But we sure make it feel like we’re together
 Because we’re scared to see each other with somebody else', [['In conjunction with the previous line, he asserts that although couples aren’t actually in love or “together” maybe in the sense of values, goals, etc. They maintain artificial relationships that are fueled by surface level interaction and convenience.

Being scared to see someone you care about with someone else, usually arises from an individual questioning whether or not that person is “as good as it gets” and whether or not they can do better and/or find their “true love”.']]), ('When a good thing goes bad it’s not the end of the world
 It’s just the end of a world that you had with one girl', [['Drake explains that when you break up with a girl, your entire life isn’t over, but instead, the moments you may be accustomed to spending with her are.

When a good thing goes bad it’s not the end of the world

A relationship doesn’t need to be romantic, it can be completely platonic but still have the same resulting feelings when it ends, often even worse. Just remember that there is still a world with seven-billion other people out there.

It’s just the end of a world that you had with one girl

Notice how Drake uses ‘a’ here, as opposed to  ‘the’ when referring to the world. He may be trying to differentiate the actual physical world from the ‘bubble’ he had been living in with the girl he is talking about.

Now that it’s over, Drake simply brushes it off as one girl in a world full of many.

The first two lines are lifted almost verbatim from the Don McLean song “When a Good Thing Goes Bad”. Lyrics from another McLean song, “The Wrong Thing to Do”, are later used in the chorus.']]), ('So cry if you need to, but I can’t stay to watch you
 That’s the wrong thing to do
 Touch if you need to, but I can’t stay to hold you
 That’s the wrong thing to do
 Talk if you need to, but I can’t stay to hear you
 That’s the wrong thing to do', [['In this song, Drake explains some of the things that happen during a breakup.  Neither of them want to stay with each other but neither of them really want to leave

In these lines, Drake is talking about how he can stay and pretend with her but it’s not right because she’ll end up getting comfortable again

This is the part of the song most directly jacked from McLean’s tune.']]), ('[Outro: Stevie Wonder on Harmonica]', [['Drizzy talked about Stevie’s contributions in an interview with The Village Voice right before Take Care’s release:

We had met and exchanged numbers a while ago so I called him when I was in LA, and he came to the studio I was working at, named Marvin’s Room. So he came and I had this song looped up named ‘Doing It Wrong,’ and it was just playing and Stevie said, ‘40 [Drake’s producing partner], turn the music up,’ and he was just vibing, being Stevie Wonder, sort of got quiet. And then he just went in the booth and brought life to this record, added all these musical pieces. He’s just, like, a dear friend of mine and a great person. I love working with him, and we’ll definitely work more in the future.

The harmonica part was used again in the track “Jorja Interlude,” on More Life.']])]

 Let’s ride the vibrations

Kind of like safety.']]), ('I got a lot of cool spots that we can go', [['In El Paso, we have a lot of spots. My favorite spot is probably Cinec Drive, El Paso, Texas. You drive all throughout the mountain, and you can look over Juarez, and you can look over El Paso, and you just see lights. It gets busy, but I just think the moment of that, seeing all these different lights—literally you see your country right next to your city—that spot is dope.']]), ('I don’t wanna fall in love off of subtweets, so
 Let’s get personal', [['This was a hint to the whole Twitter, social media connection. I remember at the time, we were talking to each other. She would always subtweet me and I would favorite it and I know it was about it. I would subtweet about her, she would favorite it, and we just kept going back and forth between this. I’m like, “I’m tired of this shit.” You can tell me all of this stuff over subtweet but you can’t text me how you feel about me? That was kind of the push to send me your location. Let’s talk in person and you can say what you were subtweeting me to my face.']]), ('Take advantage, don’t leave my heart damaged', [['That talks about just the fact that you get so comfortable, and they take advantage of everything that you’ve given them. You’ve given them your attention. Some people give their money. Your time. All of that just for the relationship to be over in three weeks. It’s like, I already poured out all my emotions to you. I already feel for you but you saw somebody else. You guys are talking on the phone. You guys are texting. And I’m still here thinking that we’re something and that’s kind of heartbreaking. It’s a hint to the reality of the situation. Even though the song sounds like it’s nice, no, this dude is really going through some shit. Like he really wants to know if this person is the right person for them, and maybe they’re not. So he ends up being fucked over eventually.']]), ('At times I wonder why I fool with you
 But this is new to me, this is new to you', [['When I was writing the song, there was always a sense of distance between the two of us. It’s like, “I like you, but I don’t know why I like you.” She likes me but, she don’t know why she likes me, because we were never really comfortable in relationships. I was only in like two relationships. She’s never been in a relationship in her whole entire life, so it was like, “Do we keep going without being in a relationship or do we give each other the title?” It’s like, why do I fool with you? We have no title. No one really knows that we’re talking but fuck it, I guess we’ll just keep talking.']]), ('Send me your location, let’s
 Focus on communicating
 ’Cause I just need the time and place to come through (place to come through)', [['The term “Send me your location,” was kind of the ode to the digital era that we’re all going through. Everything is just so controlled by phones now. It’s kind of a sense of irony because it’s like, “Send me your location so we can focus on communication,” so I can talk to you face to face. So it’s like you got to go through the phone to hit somebody up cause you’re not just going to pull up on someone’s door without telling them. It was kind of that, but then at the same time, it’s like “You know what? Let’s actually talk in real life instead of all this phone shit.”

“Let’s focus on communication" kind of has to do with breaking down that barrier that we have because everyone is just so comfortable behind their phones. We all feel the need to text everything that we feel and sometimes I feel like as individuals we lack empathy. When you talk to someone face to face, it’s almost like there’s not a lot of emotion as there was a couple of years back because everything is based off of emojis and text messages and signs and memes, which is dope. I still use that shit. But at the same time, to connect someone in the form of intimacy, I feel like it’s really necessary to kind of pick their brain, face to face, and see their reaction. Instead of seeing their emoticon.']])]

[('Your true beauty’s description; looks so good that it hurts', [['True beauty’s description sure is high praise; perhaps the only true comparison is with that of Aphrodite (or Venus), the Greek (or Roman) goddess of – among other things – beauty.

The idea that something can be so good that it’s painful is linked with the idiom “too much of a good thing”, which suggests that an excess of anything, regardless of how good, can be a negative. Despite that, I don’t think Mario is going to complain; it’s surely a pain he’ll get over quickly!']]), ('You’re a dime, plus 99, and it’s a shame
 Don’t even know what you’re worth', [['A “dime” is slang for a very attractive person. The term dime was coined to mean a perfect ten. Since this girl is “a dime plus ninety nine,” she is perfection ninety nine times over, which highlights how she could do better than the man who isn’t treating her right. The “plus ninety nine” also implies that in addition to having perfect ten looks, she has a great personality, adding to her overall value.



If this girl knew that she is more than a standard hot girl, she wouldn’t tolerate a man who cheats, she would go out and look for someone who deserves her.

This could also be interpreted as “she is valued at $1.09” [1 dime plus 99 cents] or, alternatively, 100 dimes, totaling at a grand $10. However, this interpretation is not in line with the continuity of praising this girl, so it is likely not the intended meaning.']])]
